.SH NAME
BatteryManager.charging \- BatteryManager: charging property
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Secure context:\f[R] This feature is available only in secure
contexts (HTTPS).
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]charging\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]BatteryManager\f[R] interface is a Boolean value indicating
whether or not the device\[cq]s battery is currently being charged.
When its value changes, the \f[CR]chargingchange\f[R] event is fired.
.PP
If the battery is charging or the user agent is unable to report the
battery status information, this value is \f[CR]true\f[R].
Otherwise, it is \f[CR]false\f[R].
.SH VALUE
A boolean.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]div\f[R] id=\[dq]charging\[dq]>(charging state unknown)</\f[B]div\f[R]>
.EE
.SS JavaScript
.IP
.EX
navigator.getBattery().then((battery) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[B]const\f[R] charging = battery.charging;

  document.querySelector(\[dq]#charging\[dq]).textContent = charging;
});
.EE
